<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <%- include('../partials/head', {title: "Word Reminder"})%>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/home.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Welcome to WordReminder</h1>
        <p>Your personalized word storage and reminder application</p>
        <div class="video-container">
          <iframe
            width="560"
            height="315"
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BM3nEh5LP8E"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <section class="introduction">
      <h2>Project Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        WordReminder is a Chrome extension and mobile application that allows
        users to store words they come across and receive reminders, ensuring
        better retention and learning.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Project Steps -->
    <section class="project-steps">
      <h2>Project Steps</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>1.1</strong> Using ChatGPT-4, Gemini, and multi-modal AGI
          packages to develop the WordReminder app from inception to completion.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.2</strong> What does G, P, T refer to: Generative (creating
          new content), Pre-trained (trained on large datasets), Transformer
          (handles sequences and context).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.3</strong> What is Neural Network: A set of algorithms
          modeled after the human brain to recognize patterns.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.4</strong> Algorithms: Searched various algorithms and
          selected Long Short-Term Memory Networks for my project WordReminder.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.5</strong> CASE tools: Selected GitHub for its collaborative
          features and AI-supported code assistance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.6</strong> Software model: Chose Dynamic Systems Development
          Method (DSDM) for its iterative, feedback-driven approach.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.7</strong> Code generators: Selected ChatGPT for reliable,
          contextually accurate code generation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.8</strong> Developed UMLs, implemented the project using
          open-source tools, and conducted Alpha and Beta tests.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.9</strong> Created sequence diagrams, scheduled milestones,
          and prepared a project management plan with estimated duration and
          cost.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1.10</strong> Reviewed programming languages, developed a
          basic website and app, and demonstrated the project.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <section class="summary">
      <h2>Project Summary</h2>
      <p>
        The WordReminder project was designed and implemented to provide users
        with a seamless tool to store and recall words. By leveraging modern AI
        technologies and development practices, this project offers an
        innovative way to enhance vocabulary learning.
      </p>
      <p class="credits">
        Developed by Tony Isern | CS 351 - Software Engineering II | Professor
        Aabdollah
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Call to Action -->
    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Download WordReminder</h2>
      <div class="download-buttons">
        <a
          href="https://codepen.io/optimistictrousers/pen/eYqbbPm"
          class="btn google-play"
          >Download with Google Play</a
        >
        <a
          href="https://codepen.io/optimistictrousers/pen/eYqbbPm"
          class="btn app-store"
          >Download with App Store</a
        >
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
